JO  - AMJ
SP  - 237
EP  - 258
VL  - 19
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Expectancy theory predictions of work motivation and job performance are examined. As hypothesized, predictions were materially strengthened by taking into account the effects of five boundary conditions: (a) time, (b) initial level of the criterion, (c) level of rewards, (d) task-specific ability, and (e) organizational control system responsiveness.
AB  - Expectancy theory predictions of work motivation and job performance are examined. As hypothesized, predictions were materially strengthened by taking into account the effects of five boundary conditions: (a) time, (b) initial level of the criterion, (c) level of rewards, (d) task-specific ability, and (e) organizational control system responsiveness.
