T1  - Current Status of Project Management Instruction in American Colleges And Universities
AU  - Cook, Desmond L.
AU  - Granger, James C.
Y1  - 1976/06/01
PY  - 1976
DA  - 1976/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255783
DO  - 10.5465/255783
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 323
EP  - 328
VL  - 19
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This article focuses on a study of the essence and range to which the concepts, principles and techniques of project management are currently being taught in U.S. colleges and universities. Some conclusions derived from the study states that U.S. colleges and universities are presently offering instruction in project management in both the business and engineering departments, project management is frequently taught in a regular course as opposed to a short course offering and the customary method of instruction is the lecture/discussion supplemented by individual project reports and case studies.
AB  - This article focuses on a study of the essence and range to which the concepts, principles and techniques of project management are currently being taught in U.S. colleges and universities. Some conclusions derived from the study states that U.S. colleges and universities are presently offering instruction in project management in both the business and engineering departments, project management is frequently taught in a regular course as opposed to a short course offering and the customary method of instruction is the lecture/discussion supplemented by individual project reports and case studies.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/255783
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/255783
