JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 259
EP  - 276
VL  - 19
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - A study of interrelationships among role variables, locus of control, and subordinate satisfaction and performance revealed that: (a) internals perceived less role conflict, were neither more satisfied nor performed better than externals; (b) role conflict and ambiguity explained more variance in satisfaction and performance than locus of control; and (c) role ambiguity increasingly explained more variance in job satisfaction as occupational level rose.
AB  - A study of interrelationships among role variables, locus of control, and subordinate satisfaction and performance revealed that: (a) internals perceived less role conflict, were neither more satisfied nor performed better than externals; (b) role conflict and ambiguity explained more variance in satisfaction and performance than locus of control; and (c) role ambiguity increasingly explained more variance in job satisfaction as occupational level rose.
