N2  - Survey data support several correlates of hospital administrator openness to programs of interhospital cooperation. The data fail to support the hypothesis that openness to cooperation is subject to distress motivation; rather, there is indication such openness is more likely when the administrator considers the hospital a high performer. Implications of these findings are discussed.
AB  - Survey data support several correlates of hospital administrator openness to programs of interhospital cooperation. The data fail to support the hypothesis that openness to cooperation is subject to distress motivation; rather, there is indication such openness is more likely when the administrator considers the hospital a high performer. Implications of these findings are discussed.
