N2  - A survey was conducted in five large firms during a study of barriers to minority employment. Black and white employee groups, similar in most characteristics, expressed perceptions of their treatment vis-à-vis one another in terms of hiring practices, compensation, promotion, and job satisfaction and treatment. Management implications of differing perceptions are discussed.
